The paper deals with the use of machine learning models, specifically autoencoders and heteroencoders, to improve chemical space navigation and de novo molecule generation. This falls under the intersection of computer science and chemistry, with a focus on machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
